Sweet Corn Curry

2 c corn kernels
1 pepper, chopped into small pieces (optional)
1 large onion, finely chopped
2 green chilies, slit lengthwise
1 tsp ginger garlic paste
1 tsp kasuri methi, lightly crushed (fenugreek)
1/4 tsp tumeric
1 tsp red chili powder
1 1/2 tsp coriander powder
1/4 tsp garam masala
2 finely chopped tomatoes
5 cashew nuts, soaked in 3 tbsp milk and made into smooth paste
2 tbsp fresh coriander leaves finely chopped
1 tbsp fresh cream (or malai)
salt to taste
1 1/2 tbsp oil

Heat oil in a cooking vessel. Once hot, add the onions and saute til transparent. Add green chilies and ginger garlic paste and saute for 3 min on to medium. Add peppers and saute for 5 min. Add kasuri methi and saute for 2 min. Add tumeric, red chili powder, coriander, cumin, and salt. Mix. Add the tomatoes and saute til oil separates. Add corn and mix. Place lid and cook for 4 min. Add 1/2 of the coriander and 1 1/2 c water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook for 15-18 min. Add garam masala, cashew paste and mix. Cook for 2 min. Add fresh cream and mix continuously for a min on low heat. Transfer to serving bowl and garnish with remaining coriander leaves. Serve with naan, roti, or flavored rice.
